<p>Eastern Cranston neighborhoods, including Oaklawn and Park View, often feature newer construction that may already have efficient HVAC systems but can still benefit substantially from solar installations given National Grid's high electricity rates. The Auburn and Stonington areas, with their larger lot sizes and varied roof orientations, may require customized solar designs but often have space for ground-mount systems if roof installation isn't optimal. Garden City's dense residential area presents opportunities for ductless mini-split systems that don't require extensive renovations to existing homes.</p>

